"Information is the oxygen of business. It is essential to business survival. When managed well, it can confer power, generate insight and help to facilitate competitive advantage. Yet in an information landscape defined by growing volume, higher velocity and an increasing variety of formats and sources, managing information well is a significant and complex challenge to businesses everywhere, regardless of their size or sector. Unsurprisingly, given this complexity, threats to information and its security are on the rise. In an information landscape defined by growing volume, higher velocity and an increasing variety of formats and sources, managing information well is a complex challenge. Unsurprisingly, given this complexity, threats to information and its security are on the rise. Sue Trombley of Iron Mountain examines how organisations should approach information risk management and how, when done well, this can help feed real value back into the business."
